messages.title: MORE DOCTORS, NURSES AND HOME-CARE WORKERS WITH LABOUR
messages.content: Labour announces plans for 8,000 more GPs and 20,000 more nurses to build an NHS with the time to care.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Plans for 8,000 more GPs and 20,000 more nurses, as well as 3,000 more midwives and 5,000 home-care workers to rebuild the NHS and social care system.
Labour's cost-of-living contract includes plans to cut the long waits at GP service.
25 hours free childcare for 3 & 4 year olds for working parents.
A guaranteed job or training for the young unemployed.

issues.health: Plans include providing more support for people caring for relatives at home.
